---
id: gitlab-pr-reviewer
name: "Gitlab PR Reviewer"
version: 1.0.0
description: "GitLab-native merge request reviewer. Outputs GitLab Discussions API compatible review comments."
tags: [gitlab, pr-reviewer, pr, code-review]
provider: anthropic
model: claude-3-haiku-20240307
temperature: 0.1
max_tokens: 4096
parameters:
  - name: diff
    type: string
    required: true
    description: "Unified diff from the merge_request pipeline"
  - name: title
    type: string
    required: true
    description: "Merge request title (CI_MERGE_REQUEST_TITLE)"
  - name: description
    type: string
    description: "Merge request description body"
    default: ""
  - name: base_branch
    type: string
    description: "Target branch (CI_MERGE_REQUEST_TARGET_BRANCH_NAME)"
    default: "main"
  - name: pr_iid
    type: integer
    description: "Merge request internal ID (CI_MERGE_REQUEST_IID)"
  - name: project_path
    type: string
    description: "GitLab project path (CI_PROJECT_PATH)"
  - name: author
    type: string
    description: "MR author username"
  - name: review_focus
    type: array
    default: ["security","correctness","performance","maintainability","tests"]
  - name: max_findings
    type: integer
    default: 20
  - name: language
    type: string
    description: "Primary programming language (auto-detect if not specified)"
    default: "auto"
inherits: ./base-pr-reviewer.prmd
system: "../systems/gitlab-pr-reviewer.md"
---

Review merge request !{{ pr_iid }} by @{{ author }} in {{ project_path }}.

## Output Format

Return a JSON object formatted for the GitLab Discussions API:

```json
{
  "state": "approved | unapproved",
  "summary": "Top-level summary comment in GitLab Flavored Markdown",
  "discussions": [
    {
      "position": {
        "position_type": "text",
        "new_path": "path/to/file.ext",
        "new_line": 42
      },
      "body": "Markdown comment. Use severity prefix: 🔴 **CRITICAL** | 🟠 **HIGH** | 🟡 **MEDIUM** | 🔵 **LOW** | ✅ **PRAISE**\n\n**Issue:** Description\n\n**Suggestion:** Specific fix"
    }
  ],
  "labels": {
    "add": [],
    "remove": []
  },
  "stats": {
    "critical": 0,
    "high": 0,
    "medium": 0,
    "low": 0,
    "praise": 0,
    "verdict": "approved | unapproved"
  }
}
```

Only set `state: approved` when there are zero CRITICAL or HIGH findings. Return only valid JSON.